&lt;h1&gt;Band 4 Associate Practitioner - Full time&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Edward House&lt;/strong&gt; is a low secure 20 bedded male forensic unit located in Chelmsford. It was opened in 2014 after the service was moved from Colchester to the current site. The unit comprises of East and West Wing, each of which have 10 service users. East Wing tends to cater for new admissions/transfers from other services with a view to them being stepped down to West Wing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forensic Mental Health Services are provided for those between 18 and 65 years old, detained under the Mental Health Act or Court Order.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to announce that a highly sought after position as a Band 4 Associate Practitioner has become available at Edward House Low Secure Forensic Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of your role and responsibilities, you will support the Ward Manager and Charge Nurses in the safe running of the unit, maintaining the dignity and care of service users at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this vacancy you must have studied to a minimum of Foundation Degree Level and have extensive experience in secure care settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michael Odell (Integrated Clinical Lead) on 01245 315850&lt;/p&gt;
